<title>USA: U.S. weekend box office chart -- June 13-15.</title>
<headline>U.S. weekend box office chart -- June 13-15.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Following are the final data for the top 10 movies at the June 13-15 box office, according to Exhibitor Relations Co.</p>
<p>    Film			Three-day gross    Cumulative Gross</p>
<p> 1. Speed2: Cruise Control   $16,158,942	 $  ----</p>
<p> 2. Con Air			$15,674,022	 $ 49,892,781</p>
<p> 3. The Lost World	     $12,477,515	 $190,697,964</p>
<p> 4. Addicted To Love	   $ 2,297,522	 $ 30,188,320</p>
<p> 5. Austin Powers		$ 2,092,382	 $ 46,043,157</p>
<p> 6. Gone Fishin'		 $ 2,045,965	 $ 13,803,484</p>
<p> 7. Buddy			  $ 1,917,361	 $  6,844,659</p>
<p> 8. The Fifth Element	  $ 1,483,840	 $ 57,922,135</p>
<p> 9. Trial and Error	    $ 1,343,768	 $ 11,458,185</p>
<p> 10 Breakdown		    $ 1,017,058	 $ 46,731,303</p>
<p>NOTE: &quot;Speed 2: Cruise Control&quot; is released by 20th Century Fox, a unit of News Corp.</p>
<p>&quot;Con Air&quot; and &quot;Gone Fishin'&quot; are released by Walt Disney Co.</p>
<p>&quot;The Lost World: Jurassic Park&quot; is released by Universal Pictures, a unit of Seagram Co. Ltd.</p>
<p>&quot;Addicted To Love&quot; is released by Warner Bros, a unit of Time Warner Inc.</p>
<p>&quot;Austin Powers: International Man of Mystery&quot; and &quot;Trial and Error&quot; are released by New Line Cinema, a unit of Time Warner.</p>
<p>&quot;Buddy&quot; and &quot;The Fifth Element&quot; are released by Columbia Pictures, a unit of Sony Corp.</p>
<p>&quot;Breakdown&quot; is released by Paramount Pictures, a unit of Viacom Inc..</p>
